EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT making an appropriation to the Division of Emergency
Management of the Office of the Military for the
Nonprofit Security Grant Pilot Program; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
2 General Fund to the Division of Emergency Management of the
3 Office of the Military for the Nonprofit Security Grant Pilot
4 Program created pursuant to subsection 2 the following sums:
5 For the Fiscal Year 2025-2026 ............................... $2,000,000
6 For the Fiscal Year 2026-2027 ............................... $2,000,000
7 2. The Division of Emergency Management of the Office of
8 the Military shall create the Nonprofit Security Grant Pilot Program.
9 Except as otherwise provided in subsections 3 and 4, the Division
10 shall award grants from the money appropriated by subsection 1 for
11 the Program to organizations in this State that qualify as tax-exempt
12 pursuant to section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code and are
13 at risk of threats, attacks and other violent acts to:
14 (a) Hire permanent or temporary security personnel to protect
15 the organization, including, without limitation, the physical location
16 and facilities of the organization and any person on those premises,
