1 except for costs to support security associated with travel outside
2 this State; or
3 (b) Acquire equipment to improve the security of the physical
4 location and facilities of the organization to prepare against threats,
5 attacks and other violent acts.
6 3. The Division:
7 (a) May not award a grant from the Program:
8 (1) For the purpose set forth in paragraph (a) of subsection 2,
9 of more than $10,000.
10 (2) For the purpose set forth in paragraph (b) of subsection 2,
11 of more than $50,000.
12 (3) To an organization in a fiscal year for both the purpose
13 set forth in paragraph (a) of subsection 2 and the purpose set forth in
14 paragraph (b) of subsection 2.
15 (b) Shall prioritize the award of grants from the Program to
16 organizations that:
17 (1) Are at the greatest risk of threat, attack or other violent
18 act, as determined by the Division; and
19 (2) Have not been awarded a grant from the Federal
20 Government for security personnel or equipment during the
21 immediately preceding two federal fiscal years.
22 4. The Division may:
23 (a) Apply for and accept gifts, grants and donations from any
24 source for the purpose of carrying out the Program; and
25 (b) Use not more than 5 percent of the money appropriated by
26 subsection 1 for a fiscal year to administer the Program.
27 5. Any balance of the sums appropriated by subsection 1
28 remaining at the end of the respective fiscal years must not be
29 committed for expenditure after June 30 of the respective fiscal
30 years by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
31 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
32 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
33 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
34 September 18, 2026, and September 17, 2027, respectively, by
35 either the entity to which the money was appropriated or the entity
36 to which the money was subsequently granted or transferred, and
37 must be reverted to the State General Fund on or before
38 September 18, 2026, and September 17, 2027, respectively.
39 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
